But if your second terme shall be greater than
the first, then the form of working must be changed;
as in this Example.

The proportion that is here wrought stands thus.


As the Radius, to the Sine of 23 ½;

So the Sine of 10, to the Sine of 4 gr.

If a Scale of Rumbs be thought more expedient
for these operations then is a Scale of Chords,
it may be put into some spare place of the Ruler.

¶How all re / in-clining plains (being counted as
upright in their new Latitude) are to be taken;
whether as North or South decliners.

If it fall short of 90 then is the North Pole elevated;
and the elevation is so much as the
point fals short of 90.
